tment about 50% packed, and I have decided on a pleasant two bedroom apartment near the Greensboro Arboretum.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8 size-full\" src=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/0409181107_hdr712063835.jpg\" width=\"3000\" height=\"1688\" />\r\n\r\nThe leasing agent anticipates that my lease papers will be ready by tomorrow for signing, and Thursday will be my target move-in date.\r\n\r\nIn the next few minutes, ill see about booking my moving truck, and possibly some moving help. Thankfully my furniture is pretty easy to handle.\r\n\r\nI\'ll miss Raleigh (again) but as before, I am not too far away and I plan to visit my Triangle friends often.','Moving again.','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2018-04-15 20:36:55','2018-04-16 00:36:55','',9,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/?p=13',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2018-05-06 21:55:33','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-16 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/10albumBITUSA_001-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Born in the USA album cover image\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nArtist(s): Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band\r\n\r\nAlbum: Born in the USA\r\n\r\nRelease date (USA) : June 4, 1984\r\n\r\nMost of my living has been done under city lights over the last 10 years. Lots of sirens, sidewalks, all night bars and restaurants, cookie cutter apartments, overpriced food, mild claustrophobia, and politics, politics, politics.\r\n\r\nThe world of work is also very different now. It is nice to be indoors during hard weather. My back doesn\'t ache at the end of the day anymore.\r\n\r\nIt wasn\'t always this way though. I grew up in the country; a small blue collar town called King, NC. I lived differently then. They may have rolled up the sidewalks after 8:00 pm, but there were mountain roads to cruise under the moonlight. The warm spring nights were fill