ton DC to Chicago IL, to Raton, NM and finally to Denver, CO.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/simpleMap.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-40\" src=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/simpleMap.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1470\" height=\"696\" /></a>\r\n\r\n...More to come!','To Colorado by rail.','','inherit','closed','closed','','35-revision-v1','','','2018-06-18 15:10:17','2018-06-18 19:10:17','',35,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/?p=41',0,'revision','',0),(44,1,'2018-07-14 23:09:02','2018-07-15 03:09:02','I am about to take my first international trip to Halifax, Nova Scotia. Though this is a business trip, I am going to use any downtime to see and experience as much as I can. The trip will begin on Tuesday, July 17 and I will return home on Monday, July 23.\r\n<h2>Contents</h2>\r\n<a href=\"#Wednesday, June 6, 2018\">Wednesday, June 6, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Thursday, July 5, 2018\">Thursday, July 5, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Sunday, July 15, 2018\">Sunday, July 15, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Monday, July 16, 2018\">Monday, July 16, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Tuesday, July 17, 2018\">Tuesday, July 17, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Wednesday, July 18, 2018\">Wednesday, July 18, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued\">Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Thursday, July 19, 2018\">Thursday, July 19, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Friday, July 20, 2018\">Friday, July 20, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Saturday, July 21, 2018\">Saturday, July 21, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Sunday, July 22, 2018\">Sunday, July 22, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Monday, July 23, 2018\">Monday, July 23, 2018</a>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Wednesday, June 6, 2018\"></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Tuesday, July 17, 2018</h2>\r\n6:10 AM.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Managed to fall asleep around 9:30 last night.</li>\r\n 	<li>Alarm went off at 3:45. Printed out my boarding passes for this leg. Left apartment by 4:45 (I felt like I was pushing it since boarding for flight begins at 530).</li>\r\n 	<li>PTI is only 5 miles from my apartment and no traffic at this time of morning.</li>\r\n 	<li>Parked car in long term lot close to terminal.</li>\r\n 	<li>Found out at ticket counter that my flight has been delayed by 1 hour (no biggie since layover in Newark was going to be long)</li>\r\n 	<li>TSA screening went smoothly.</li>\r\n 	<li>Grabbed a breakfast sandwich and an iced tea. (I must remember: RECEIPTS RECEIPTS RECEIPTS!! I am so used to just balling them up and trashing them.</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight Delayed until 7:30 AM\r\n7:30 AM</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight from Greensboro, NC to Newark, NJ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'72\']\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n8:45 AM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Just arrived in Newark. First flight went well (but the landing gear on that plane sounds in need of a brake job.)</li>\r\n 	<li>TROUBLE: Connecting flight to Halifax CANCELLED!!</li>\r\n 	<li>Spoke with airline,  that they could give me is a 2:10 flight to Montreal, then another connecting flight to Halifax. I went with it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proceeded to terminal via tram and waited...</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight was on the verge of cancellation due to weather in New York. Delayed several times during my wait, but we finally boarded at 4:30 and left at 5pm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n5:00 PM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Flight from Newark, NJ to Montreal, QC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'83\']\r\n\r\n6:00 PM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Pretty nauseating flight; lots of turbulence.</li>\r\n 	<li>Unable to get through customs in time for the 6:45 flight to Halifax.</li>\r\n 	<li>Airline unable to find any other flights other than a 7:35 flight tomorrow morning. I booked it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Found a vacant room at a nearby Holiday Inn.</li>\r\n 	<li>Disappointed that I will have to miss some of the morning presentations at my conference. Hope to make it there by noon tomorrow.[slide-anything id=\'91\']</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name=\"Wednesday, July 18, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Wednesday, July 18, 2018</h2>\r\n1:50 PM - Montréal–Pierre Elliott Trudeau International Airport\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Woes continue. Arrived at terminal to learn that my 7:45 reservation had been cancelled. (CRAAAAPPPP!!!!)\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>After a while on the phone with customer support, the most I could get out of them was \"Unspecified Technical Error\". They would not give further information.</li>\r\n 	<li>I suspect the glitch had something to do with the crazy way the ticketing agents had to go about rescheduling and tying in different carriers (United vs Air Canada, Westjet, etc.)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Only flight they have available for Halifax doesn\'t board until 3:35 PM, and arrives in Halifax at 6:10 PM.</li>\r\n 	<li>I will be missing the entire first day of the conference, but I think I can catch up.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>I made contact with my colleague (who somehow had no travel issues yesterday???) and he is sending me the items covered via email.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Spending the day in the terminal, killing time.<a href=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/0718181428.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-102\" src=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/0718181428.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" /></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name=\"Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued\"></a>\r\n<h2>Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued</h2>\r\n6:15 PM (Halifax Time)\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Landed in Halifax. My coworker met me at the airport to drive me to the hotel.</li>\r\n 	<li>Checked in to room and went for dinner at a local pub\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The name of the pub was \"The Press Gang\", I learned that the owners chose this name since Halifax had a history of using Impressment to fill their naval ranks. Wikipedia article <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impressment_(Nova_Scotia)\">here</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'562\']\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Thursday, July 19, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Thursday, July 19, 2018</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Second day of conference at Saint Mary\'s University. I was able to catch up on what I missed from Day 1.</li>\r\n 	<li>For dinner, we met at The Wooden Monkey (explanation of the name <a href=\"https://www.thecoast.ca/RestaurantandBarNews/archives/2014/11/06/whats-in-a-name-the-wooden-monkey\">here.</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Explored a few streets before heading back to hotel room.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'566\']\r\n<a name=\"Friday, July 20, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Friday, July 20, 2018</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Last day of the conference.</li>\r\n 	<li>For dinner, we met at The Henry House (history <a href=\"https://henryhouse.ca/wordpress/about-the-henry-house/\">here</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'573\']\r\n<a name=\"Saturday, July 21, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Saturday, July 21, 2018</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>To save some cash, I booked a room at Dalhousie University (They rent their open dorms to travelers during the summer months).</li>\r\n 	<li>Booked an evening harbor tour on The Tall Ship Silva.\r\n[slide-anything id=\'580\'][slide-anything id=\'577\']</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Sunday, July 22, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Sunday, July 22, 2018</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Last day in Halifax. Visited the Maritime Museum of the Atlantic.</li>\r\n 	<li>Finished the day with a tour via amphibious vehicle.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'583\']\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Monday, July 23, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Monday, July 23, 2018</h2>\r\n\r\n5:00 AM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Didn\'t sleep well, decided to take an early morning walk around town.</li>\r\n 	<li>Breakfast at Tim Horton\'s.9:00 AM</li>\r\n 	<li>Took taxi to airport. Flight delayed until 12:30pm2:30 PM</li>\r\n 	<li>Arrived at Boston Logan International Airport. Connecting flight to LaGuardia delayed until approx 5:30pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n7:30 PM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Arrived at LaGuardia International Airport. Met connecting flight to Greensboro at 8:00</li>\r\n 	<li>10:30 PMLanded in Greensboro. Was home by 11. I was asleep before my head even hit the pillow.</li>\r\n</ul>','Halifax, Nova Scotia: July 2018','','publish','open','open','','halifax-nova-scotia-july-2018','','','2018-07-25 09:05:52','2018-07-25 13:05:52','',0,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/?p=44',0,'post','',0),(45,1,'2018-07-14 22:09:40','2018-07-15 02:09:40','','001_halifax_trip','','inherit','open','closed','','001_halifax_trip','','','2018-07-14 22:09:40','2018-07-15 02:09:40','',44,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/001_halifax_trip.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(46,1,'2018-07-14 22:56:58','2018-07-15 02:56:58','','002_halifax_trip','Weather is looking pretty good for the most part.','inherit','open','closed','','002_halifax_trip','','','2018-07-14 22:57:22','2018-07-15 02:57:22','',44,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/002_halifax_trip.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(47,1,'2018-07-14 23:09:02','2018-07-15 03:09:02','Saturday, July 14, 2018.\r\n\r\nMy first passport arrived in the mail a few weeks ago. With that, I am all set for my trip to Halifax, Nova Scotia next week.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/002_halifax_trip.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-46 size-full\" src=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/002_halifax_trip.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1270\" height=\"666\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe Weather is looking pretty good for the most part.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Halifax, Nova Scotia: July 2018','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-v1','','','2018-07-14 23:09:02','2018-07-15 03:09:02','',44,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/?p=47',0,'revision','',0),(48,1,'2018-07-14 23:19:05','2018-07-15 03:19:05','','Sample Slider','','publish','closed','closed','','sample-slider','','','2018-07-14 23:19:05','2018-07-15 