n to her office and went over my paperwork.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, it turned out the birth certificate I brought was not official, but lucky for me, the vital records office was next door. With a $20 fee, they were able to print me out an official one.\r\n\r\nI returned to the passport office with it. The clerk then photographed me (not available at all locations!) and took my payment.\r\n\r\nI think all together, I spent $250 (including the birth cert fee, expedited fee, etc)\r\n\r\nI was finished by about 11am.\r\n\r\nSince my employer reimburses travel expenses, it will be up to me to furnish the upfront money for the airline tickets, hotel, food, etc. I usually avoid credit cards all together, but the reality is that there are times as an adult when they are damn near required. Since I do not plan on holding a balance for very long, I would like to get in on the crunching game and start earning points or frequent flyer miles. This <a href=\"https://www.nerdwallet.com/card-details/card-name/BankAmericard-Travel-Rewards\">article</a> on Nerdwallet guided me to the Bank of America Travel Card. Since I already have an account with Bank of America, I decided to go with it intending to meet the purchase amount necessary to gain the 20000 bonus point offer. (THIS IS A DANGEROUS GAME, I know, but since I HAVE to spend the money, might as well generate some points!!)\r\n\r\nThe Weather is looking pretty good for the most part.\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Thursday, July 5, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Thursday, July 5, 2018</h2>\r\nMy passport and travel credit card have arrived. It is now time to book my trip.\r\n\r\nI used Expedia to book the appropriate hotel and flight. For the duration of the conference, I will be staying at the Cambridge Suites hotel. I have also decided to stay over the weekend in order to do some exploring and sightseeing. For the last few nights of my trip, I will be staying in a dorm room at Dalhousie University (They rent out their empty dorm rooms during the summer at incredible prices!!)\r\n<h2>Sunday, July 15, 2018</h2>\r\nTwo days to trip\r\n<a name=\"Monday, July 16, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Monday, July 16, 2018</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Call my bank to let them know that there may be some charges made in Canada soon (avoid triggering fraud prevention locks)</span> DONE 10am</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Pick up business cards and pack</span> Done 11am</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Check out GoPro for trip</span> Done 10am</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Check in to outbound flight.</span> Done 12pm</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Verify reservation with Cambridge Suites.</span> Done 2pm</li>\r\n 	<li>Visit major bank (not mine unfortunately) to obtain some Canadian cash (NO-GO: I should have done this sooner, but no big deal. ATM should get me by initially)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name=\"Tuesday, July 17, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Tuesday, July 17, 2018</h2>\r\n6:10 AM.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Managed to fall asleep around 9:30 last night.</li>\r\n 	<li>Alarm went off at 3:45. Printed out my boarding passes for this leg. Left apartment by 4:45 (I felt like I was pushing it since boarding for flight begins at 530).</li>\r\n 	<li>PTI is only 5 miles from my apartment and no traffic at this time of morning.</li>\r\n 	<li>Parked car in long term lot close to terminal.</li>\r\n 	<li>Found out at ticket counter that my flight has been delayed by 1 hour (no biggie since layover in Newark was going to be long)</li>\r\n 	<li>TSA screening went smoothly.</li>\r\n 	<li>Grabbed a breakfast sandwich and an iced tea. (I must remember: RECEIPTS RECEIPTS RECEIPTS!! I am so used to just balling them up and trashing them.</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight Delayed until 7:30 AM\r\n7:30 AM</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight from Greensboro, NC to Newark, NJ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'72\']\r\n\r\n</break>\r\n\r\n8:45 A