personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/0722181621_HDR.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(554,1,'2018-07-22 22:37:49','2018-07-23 02:37:49','','0722181621d_HDR','','inherit','open','closed','','0722181621d_hdr','','','2018-07-22 22:37:49','2018-07-23 02:37:49','',0,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/0722181621d_HDR.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(555,1,'2018-07-22 22:37:57','2018-07-23 02:37:57','','0722181621e_HDR','','inherit','open','closed','','0722181621e_hdr','','','2018-07-22 22:37:57','2018-07-23 02:37:57','',0,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/0722181621e_HDR.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(559,1,'2018-07-23 03:02:17','2018-07-23 07:02:17','1.09','','','_n59t_dwwp','closed','closed','','559','','','2018-07-23 03:02:17','2018-07-23 07:02:17','',0,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/?p=559',0,'_','',0),(560,1,'2018-07-22 23:39:03','2018-07-23 03:39:03','','PressGang','','inherit','open','closed','','pressgang','','','2018-07-23 00:07:58','2018-07-23 04:07:58','',562,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/PressGang.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(561,1,'2018-07-22 23:40:20','2018-07-23 03:40:20','','wooden','','inherit','open','closed','','wooden','','','2018-07-23 00:29:18','2018-07-23 04:29:18','',566,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/wooden.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(562,1,'2018-07-23 00:06:34','2018-07-23 04:06:34','','WednesdayEvening','','publish','closed','closed','','tuesdayevening','','','2018-07-25 08:54:44','2018-07-25 12:54:44','',0,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/?post_type=sa_slider&#038;p=562',0,'sa_slider','',0),(563,1,'2018-07-23 00:17:09','2018-07-23 04:17:09','I am about to take my first international trip to Halifax, Nova Scotia. Though this is a business trip, I am going to use any downtime to see and experience as much as I can. The trip will begin on Tuesday, July 17 and I will return home on Monday, July 23.\r\n<h2>Contents</h2>\r\n<a href=\"#Wednesday, June 6, 2018\">Wednesday, June 6, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Thursday, July 5, 2018\">Thursday, July 5, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Sunday, July 15, 2018\">Sunday, July 15, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Monday, July 16, 2018\">Monday, July 16, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Tuesday, July 17, 2018\">Tuesday, July 17, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Wednesday, July 18, 2018\">Wednesday, July 18, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued\">Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Thursday, July 19, 2018\">Thursday, July 19, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Friday, July 20, 2018\">Friday, July 20, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Saturday, July 21, 2018\">Saturday, July 21, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Sunday, July 22, 2018\">Sunday, July 22, 2018</a>\r\n<a href=\"#Monday, July 23, 2018\">Monday, July 23, 2018</a>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Wednesday, June 6, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Wednesday, June 6, 2018</h2>\r\nMy preparations began in earnest on June 6, 2018 as I needed to obtain a passport. I took the day off from work in order to handle as many of the passport application logistics as possible in one day. A great resource was an article linked <a href=\"https://www.wikihow.com/Get-a-U.S.-Passport\">here</a>. I found my original birth certificate that the hospital gave my mother (Found out it was not official. I should have gone <a href=\"http://www.guilfordcountync.gov/our-county/register-of-deeds/vital-records/birth\">here</a> instead.) and filled out the application paperwork. There were a few places in Guilford County that feature passport acceptance services, but I decided to go to the primary office in Downtown Greensboro (site link <a href=\"http://www.guilfordcountync.gov/our-county/register-of-deeds/passport-services\">here</a>.)\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_61\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"550\"]<a href=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ShowImage.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-61\" src=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ShowImage.jpeg\" alt=\"Image of Downtown Greensboro Passport Acceptance Office.\" width=\"550\" height=\"412\" /></a> Downtown Greensboro Passport Application Acceptance Office.[/caption]\r\n\r\nI arrived at about 930 AM and parked in one of the downtown parking decks. The office was not very crowded, only one person ahead of me. Once they had finished, the clerk brought me in to her office and went over my paperwork.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, it turned out the birth certificate I brought was not official, but lucky for me, the vital records office was next door. With a $20 fee, they were able to print me out an official one.\r\n\r\nI returned to the passport office with it. The clerk then photographed me (not available at all locations!) and took my payment.\r\n\r\nI think all together, I spent $250 (including the birth cert fee, expedited fee, etc)\r\n\r\nI was finished by about 11am.\r\n\r\nSince my employer reimburses travel expenses, it will be up to me to furnish the upfront money for the airline tickets, hotel, food, etc. I usually avoid credit cards all together, but the reality is that there are times as an adult when they are damn near required. Since I do not plan on holding a balance for very long, I would like to get in on the crunching game and start earning points or frequent flyer miles. This <a href=\"https://www.nerdwallet.com/card-details/card-name/BankAmericard-Travel-Rewards\">article</a> on Nerdwallet guided me to the Bank of America Travel Card. Since I already have an account with Bank of America, I decided to go with it intending to meet the purchase amount necessary to gain the 20000 bonus point offer. (THIS IS A DANGEROUS GAME, I know, but since I HAVE to spend the money, might as well generate some points!!)\r\n\r\nThe Weather is looking pretty good for the most part.\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Thursday, July 5, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Thursday, July 5, 2018</h2>\r\nMy passport and travel credit card have arrived. It is now time to book my trip.\r\n\r\nI used Expedia to book the appropriate hotel and flight. For the duration of the conference, I will be staying at the Cambridge Suites hotel. I have also decided to stay over the weekend in order to do some exploring and sightseeing. For the last few nights of my trip, I will be staying in a dorm room at Dalhousie University (They rent out their empty dorm rooms during the summer at incredible prices!!)\r\n<h2>Sunday, July 15, 2018</h2>\r\nTwo days until trip. Doing most of my packing today.\r\n<a name=\"Monday, July 16, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Monday, July 16, 2018</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Call my bank to let them know that there may be some charges made in Canada soon (avoid triggering fraud prevention locks)</span> DONE 10am</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Pick up business cards and pack</span> Done 11am</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Check out GoPro for trip</span> Done 10am</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Check in to outbound flight.</span> Done 12pm</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Verify reservation with Cambridge Suites.</span> Done 2pm</li>\r\n 	<li>Visit major bank (not mine unfortunately) to obtain some Canadian cash (NO-GO: I should have done this sooner, but no big deal. ATM should get me by initially)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name=\"Tuesday, July 17, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Tuesday, July 17, 2018</h2>\r\n6:10 AM.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Managed to fall asleep around 9:30 last night.</li>\r\n 	<li>Alarm went off at 3:45. Printed out my boarding passes for this leg. Left apartment by 4:45 (I felt like I was pushing it since boarding for flight begins at 530).</li>\r\n 	<li>PTI is only 5 miles from my apartment and no traffic at this time of morning.</li>\r\n 	<li>Parked car in long term lot close to terminal.</li>\r\n 	<li>Found out at ticket counter that my flight has been delayed by 1 hour (no biggie since layover in Newark was going to be long)</li>\r\n 	<li>TSA screening went smoothly.</li>\r\n 	<li>Grabbed a breakfast sandwich and an iced tea. (I must remember: RECEIPTS RECEIPTS RECEIPTS!! I am so used to just balling them up and trashing them.</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight Delayed until 7:30 AM\r\n7:30 AM</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight from Greensboro, NC to Newark, NJ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'72\']\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n8:45 AM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Just arrived in Newark. First flight went well (but the landing gear on that plane sounds in need of a brake job.)</li>\r\n 	<li>TROUBLE: Connecting flight to Halifax CANCELLED!!</li>\r\n 	<li>Spoke with airline,  that they could give me is a 2:10 flight to Montreal, then another connecting flight to Halifax. I went with it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proceeded to terminal via tram and waited...</li>\r\n 	<li>Flight was on the verge of cancellation due to weather in New York. Delayed several times during my wait, but we finally boarded at 4:30 and left at 5pm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n5:00 PM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Flight from Newark, NJ to Montreal, QC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[slide-anything id=\'83\']\r\n\r\n6:00 PM\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Pretty nauseating flight; lots of turbulence.</li>\r\n 	<li>Unable to get through customs in time for the 6:45 flight to Halifax.</li>\r\n 	<li>Airline unable to find any other flights other than a 7:35 flight tomorrow morning. I booked it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Found a vacant room at a nearby Holiday Inn.</li>\r\n 	<li>Disappointed that I will have to miss some of the morning presentations at my conference. Hope to make it there by noon tomorrow.[slide-anything id=\'91\']</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name=\"Wednesday, July 18, 2018\"></a>\r\n<h2>Wednesday, July 18, 2018</h2>\r\n1:50 PM - Montréal–Pierre Elliott Trudeau International Airport\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Woes continue. Arrived at terminal to learn that my 7:45 reservation had been cancelled. (CRAAAAPPPP!!!!)\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>After a while on the phone with customer support, the most I could get out of them was \"Unspecified Technical Error\". They would not give further information.</li>\r\n 	<li>I suspect the glitch had something to do with the crazy way the ticketing agents had to go about rescheduling and tying in different carriers (United vs Air Canada, Westjet, etc.)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Only flight they have available for Halifax doesn\'t board until 3:35 PM, and arrives in Halifax at 6:10 PM.</li>\r\n 	<li>I will be missing the entire first day of the conference, but I think I can catch up.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>I made contact with my colleague (who somehow had no travel issues yesterday???) and he is sending me the items covered via email.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Spending the day in the terminal, killing time.<a href=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/0718181428.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-102\" src=\"http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/0718181428.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" /></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name=\"Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued\"></a>\r\n<h2>Wednesday, July 18, 2018 Continued /h2&gt;</h2>\r\n<h2>Thursday, July 19, 2018</h2>\r\nEntry coming soon\r\n<h2>Friday, July 20, 2018</h2>\r\nEntry coming soon\r\n<h2>Saturday, July 21, 2018</h2>\r\nEntry coming soon\r\n<h2>Sunday, July 22, 2018</h2>\r\nEntry coming soon\r\n<h2>Monday, July 23, 2018</h2>','Halifax, Nova Scotia: July 2018','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-v1','','','2018-07-23 00:17:09','2018-07-23 04:17:09','',44,'http://www.donniehardin.com/personalblog/?p=563',0,'revision','',0),(564,1,'2018-07-23 00:18:39','2018-07-23 04:18:39','I am about to take my first international trip to Halifax, Nova Scotia. Though this is a business trip, I am going to use any downtime to see and experience as much as I can. The trip will begin on Tuesday, July 17 and I 